Preheat your #oven{} to 180℃. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}(thinly sliced). Cut the @lime{1/2}(cut into 4 wedges) into 4 wedges. Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%can} in a #colander{}. Pop half the kidney beans into a #bowl{} and roughly crush with the back of a #fork{}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} over medium high heat Add the onions and fry until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the sliced mushrooms to the pan. Fry for ~{4-5%minutes} until they soften and start to colour.

Meanwhile, add another small glug of oil then stir the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g}, @ground cumin{1%tsp}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp} and kidney beans (both crushed and whole) into the mushrooms and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the @water{75%ml} and @vegetable stock powder{1%tsp}. Stir well to dissolve the stock paste. Cook for a further ~{5-6%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then turn the heat to low while you finish everything else off!

Put the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and @chipotle paste{20%g} in a small bowl (careful the chipotle is hot - use less if you don't like heat!). Mix well. Loosen the mayo with a splash of water (it needs to be able to drizzle!) Season to taste with a squeeze of lime.

Pop the @plain taco tortillas{3} directly onto the top shelf of the oven for ~{1-2%minutes} just to heat through (2 per person). Crumble the @feta cheese{100%g}. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1}(trimmed and halved lengthways) then half lengthways. Thinly slice widthways and toss with a squeeze of lime juice.

Lay a warm tortilla on a #board{} or #plate{}. Add a handful of lettuce to the base. Start with a couple of spoonfuls of the bean and mushroom mix on top. Finish with a sprinkle of feta and a good drizzle of the chipotle mayo. Fold in half and transfer to a plate. Repeat with the other tortillas. You should serve two per person. Serve with any extra lime wedges. Dig in!